deleverageAccount(address,address,addres.notice: If an account is below the minimum collateral ratio, this method wil deleverage (liquidate) that account. `depositAmountExternal` in the borrow currency will be transferred from the liquidator and used to offset the account's debt position. The liquidator will receive either vaultShares or cash depending.

params.account: the address that will exit the vault
params.depositAmountExternal: amount of asset cash to deposit
params.liquidator: the address that will receive profits from liquidation
params.redeemData: calldata sent to the vault when redeeming liquidator profits
params.transferSharesToLiquidator: transfers the shares to the liquidator instead of redeeming them

returns.profitFromLiquidation: amount of vaultShares or cash received from liquidation

enterVault(address,address,uint256,uint2.notice: Borrows a specified amount of fCash in the vault's borrow currency and deposits it all plus the depositAmountExternal into the vault to mint strategy tokens.

params.account: the address that will enter the vault
params.depositAmountExternal: some amount of additional collateral in the borrowed currency to be transferred to vault
params.maxBorrowRate: maximum interest rate to borrow at
params.vaultData: additional data to pass to the vault contract

returns.strategyTokensAdded: the total strategy tokens added to the maturity, including any tokens from settlement. Allows enterVault to be used by off-chain methods to get an accurate simulation of the strategy tokens minted.

exitVault(address,address,address,uint25.notice: Prior to maturity, allows an account to withdraw their position from the vault. Will redeem some number of vault shares to the borrow currency and close the borrow position by lending `fCashToLend`. Any shortfall in cash from lending will be transferred from the account, any excess profits will be transferred to the account. Post maturity, will net off the account's debt against vault cash balances and redeem all remaining strategy tokens back to the borrowed currency and transfer the profits to the account.

params.account: the address that will exit the vault
params.exitVaultData: passed to the vault during exit
params.minLendRate: the minimum rate to lend at
params.receiver: the address that will receive profits
params.vaultSharesToRedeem: amount of vault tokens to exit, only relevant when exiting pre-maturity

returns.underlyingToReceiver: amount of underlying tokens returned to the receiver on exit

rollVaultPosition(address,address,uint25.notice: Re-enters the vault at a longer dated maturity. The account's existing borrow position will be closed and a new borrow position at the specified maturity will be opened. Strategy token holdings will transfer to the longer dated maturity.

params.account: the address that will reenter the vault
params.depositAmountExternal: amount to deposit into the new maturity
params.fCashToBorrow: amount of fCash to borrow in the next maturity
params.maxBorrowRate: slippage protection for new borrow position

returns.strategyTokensAdded: the total strategy tokens added to the maturity, including any tokens rolled from the previous maturity.. Allows rollVaultPosition to be used by off-chain methods to get an accurate simulation of the strategy tokens minted.
